def: A small town. North Brit. Rev.
A magpie; a piet. [Prov. Eng.]Here cometh the worthy prelate as pert as a pyet. Sir W. Scott.
A work having two parapets whose faces unite so as to form asalient angle toward the enemy.
Beforehand; antecedently; as, a plan previously formed.
Tightly; nimbly. [Obs.] "I have seen him trip it tithly." Beau.& Fl.

A member of one of the great family of Negroid tribes occupyingequatorial and southern Africa. These tribes include, as importantdivisions, the Kafirs, Damaras, Bechuanas, and many tribes whosenames begin with Aba-, Ama-, Ba-, Ma-, Wa-, variants of the Bantuplural personal prefix Aba-, as in Ba-ntu, or Aba-ntu, itself acombination of this prefix with the syllable -ntu, a person. --Ban"tu, a.
Producing, or favoring the production of, urine.
Anger; madness; insanity; rage. [Obs.] Spenser.Woodness laughing in his rage. Chaucer.

A weight of 29.166 + grams used in assaying, for convenience.Since it bears the same relation to the milligram that a ton of 2000avoirdupois pounds does to the troy ounce, the weight in milligramsof precious metal obtained from an assay ton of ore gives directlythe number of ounces to the ton.
Pertaining to, or inhabiting, the Ganges; as, the Gangeticshark.
